{{Quote|Then the Emperor took over the facility. At first it wasn't so bad, but now&hellip; It's called EmPal SuRecon now &mdash; Emperor's Surgical Reconstruction Center. We started turning away non-human patients. The best doctors and personnel started to quit, and they recruited others.|[[Malory Lands]], to [[Ferus Olin]]|<ref name="Against the Empire">''[[The Last of the Jedi: Against the Empire]]''</ref>}}
The '''Chancellor Palpatine Surgical Reconstruction Center''', sometimes shortened to '''ChanPal SuRecon Center''', was crowned one of the tallest buildings on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], it was also known as the '''Grand Republic Medical Facility''' or simply as the '''Grand Medical Facility'''. It later became known as the '''Emperor Palpatine Surgical Reconstruction Center''', being commonly referred to as the '''EmPal SuRecon Center'''. It was an imposing spire that dominated its particular stretch of the [[Galactic City/Legends|Galactic City]]&mdash;later [[Galactic City/Legends|Imperial City]]&mdash;skyline.

==History==
===Dark designs===
[[File:WizardCastsSoulTrap-SWV.jpg|thumb|left|150px|[[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] performing [[Sith alchemy/Legends|Sith alchemy]] and [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] rituals within the center]]
The [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] stronghold hid in plain sight with large [[Window/Legends|windows]] that seemed to show that there was nothing to hide. In addition, it relied on the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi's]] reluctance to attack a [[Medcenter/Legends|hospital]] and risk the patients inside. It featured four landing pads for emergency cases near the top of the structure. The interior was lined with ultradense walls of [[Neuranium/Legends|neuranium]] shielding to conceal any [[Radiation/Legends|radiation]] leak from the building's [[Reactor/Legends|reactor]]. Surrounding this shielding was an exterior shell of [[Durasteel/Legends|durasteel]] armored with a [[Lanthanide/Legends|lanthanide]] and [[Duralium/Legends|duralium]] alloy. [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] performed acts of [[Sith alchemy/Legends|Sith alchemy]] within the ChanPal SuRecon.

===Darth Vader===
This gloomy location was the site of [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader's]] rebuilding. After Darth Vader's [[Duel on Mustafar/Legends|duel]] with his former [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]], [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]], Darth Sidious brought his badly wounded [[Sith apprentice/Legends|apprentice]] via [[Theta-class T-2c shuttle/Legends|shuttle]] to the Reconstruction Center where he was to be rebuilt. During the duel, Vader had sustained near-fatal third-degree burns, severe lung damage and the loss of his remaining limbs, as well as emotional pain.

The damage to his body would be repaired through intensive [[Cybernetics/Legends|cybernetic]] enhancement at the main laboratory. Palpatine also ordered the [[Medical droid/Legends|medical droids]]&mdash;two [[2-1B surgical droid/Legends|2-1B surgical droids]], one [[FX-6 medical assistant droid]], and one [[DD-13 medical assistant droid/Legends|DD-13 cybernetic surgical droid]]&mdash;to keep Vader awake during the process so the pain would make him stronger. Many of these droids had either participated in or observed the transformation of Qymaen jai Sheelal into [[Grievous/Legends|Grievous]].

[[File:SWCL_EmPalSuRecon.jpg|thumb|right|200px|SuRecon Center]]
Upon his revival as a [[Cyborg/Legends|cyborg]], Vader questioned his master about [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]]. Sidious replied that Vader had killed his wife in his anger. Overwhelmed by his despair in the belief he had killed his wife and their unborn child, Vader broke his bindings on the operating table and struggled to walk under the power of his new mechanical legs. His [[Force scream/Legends|rage]] destroyed the medical droids that had saved his life and severely damaged the interior of the main laboratory. It also caused a worker to go deaf permanently.

The workers didn't know it was Vader who was being worked on. They thought it had been either a [[Ghost (folklore)/Legends|ghost]] or all the beings who had been killed in the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] screaming one last scream. This rumor continued through [[18 BBY/Legends|18 BBY]].

===Galactic Empire===
[[File:SWCL_Sith_Medcenter.jpg|thumb|left|260px|SuRecon Center cutaway]]
In the first [[Standard month/Legends|months]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] Palpatine used the EmPal SuRecon Center as his headquarters. He hosted meetings with members of the [[Imperial Senate/Legends|Imperial Senate]] in a [[Imperial throne room (Emperor Palpatine Surgical Reconstruction Center)|throne room]] below his private chamber and Sith medical facility. He eventually moved his base of operations to the [[Imperial Palace/Legends|Imperial Palace]] once it had been rebuilt to his specifications. Darth Vader returned to the facility for repairs to his prosthetic right arm, damaged in a duel with [[Bol Chatak]] on [[Murkhana/Legends|Murkhana]].

Later in the reign of the Empire, the EmPal SuRecon Center became known to citizens as one of the most prestigious medical treatment centers in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. Its architecture included [[VLD2261 long-range heavy blaster defense battery/Legends|VLD2261 laser cannons]], [[Emperor's Royal Guard/Legends|Royal Guard]] emplacements, a [[Palpatine's meditation chamber/Legends|private meditation chamber]] for Palpatine, and other facilities used for training [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]]. [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]] [[Lightsaber crystal/Legends|lightsaber crystals]], [[Sith scroll/Legends|Sith scrolls]], powerful [[Sith artifact/Legends|Sith artifacts]], bio-details of hundreds of generations of Sith, and a [[Vergence/Legends|dark force reservoir]] were also housed in the building's center.

